rporation|Hal Leonard Corporation]]|isbn=9781480393318|access-date=2022-02-02|archive-date=2022-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425115752/https://books.google.com/books?id=wuUiBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT246v}}</ref><ref name="mw">{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter's "Bad Day" Is Best-Selling Digital Song of All Time|url=http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/daniel-powters-bad-day-is-best-selling-digital-song-of-all-time-696356.htm|access-date=2014-12-14|date=2006-07-19|publisher=[[Marketwired|Marketwired]]|archive-date=2018-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705073539/http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/daniel-powters-bad-day-is-best-selling-digital-song-of-all-time-696356.htm}}</ref>。這首歌以[[降E大調|降E大調]]創作，使用[[十六分音符|十六分音符]]的[[切分音|切分音]]節奏<ref name="hal" />。根據華納兄弟在Musicnotes.com發布的樂譜，帕德的[[音域|音域]]範圍穿梭在E♭<sub>3</sub>和[[D♭_(音名)|D♭]]<sub>5</sub>之間<sub><ref>{{cite web|title=Bad Day By Daniel Powter - Digital Sheet Music|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0067708|access-date=2016-01-20|date=2008-09-08|publisher=Musicnotes.com|archive-date=2022-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220407163416/https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0067708}}</ref></sub>。歌曲的配器法不同於「青少年力推的許多搖滾樂」<ref name="ct">{{cite journal|title=Reviews: Singles|author=Taylor, Chuck|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HhYEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA60|date=2006-03-18|journal=[[Billboard_(magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus_Global_Media|Prometheus Global Media]]|issue=11|volume=118|page=60|access-date=2022-02-02|archive-date=2022-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220501002607/https://books.google.com/books?id=HhYEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA60}}</ref>，然則包含帕德所說的「強勢」的鼓<ref name="cbs" />。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的大衛·布朗（David Browne）稱歌曲是：「寫給任何感到沮喪的人……但（相比之下）它大張旗鼓的全景編排想讓你振作起來」<ref>{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2006/04/10/daniel-powter|access-date=2015-02-05|author=Browne, David|date=2006-04-10|work=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time_Inc.|Time Inc.]]|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203233342/https://ew.com/article/2006/04/10/daniel-powter/}}</ref>。《{{Le|曼徹斯特晚報|Manchester Evening News}}》的西蒙·多諾霍（Simon Donohue）評述它的聲音「從男孩樂團的庸俗過渡到[[幽浮一族樂團|幽浮一族樂團]]風格的嘶啞搖滾」<ref>{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter – Bad Day (Warner Bros.)|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/music/daniel-powter---bad-day-1074079|access-date=2015-02-11|author=Donohue, Simon|date=2005-07-01|work=[[Manchester_Evening_News|Manchester Evening News]]|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203074358/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/music/daniel-powter---bad-day-1074079}}</ref>''。''據[[PopMatters|PopMatters]]的溫斯頓·孔（Winston Kung）所言，它「切合[[时代精神|时代精神]]」<ref name="popm">{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter: Daniel Powter|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/daniel_powter_daniel_powter/|access-date=2015-01-16|author=Kung, Wiston|date=2006-04-26|work=[[PopMatters|PopMatters]]|archive-date=2017-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620132846/http://www.popmatters.com/review/daniel_powter_daniel_powter/}}</ref>。

《[[英國廣播公司新聞網|BBC新聞雜誌]]》的艾倫·康納（Alan Connor）稱〈壞天氣〉的歌詞具有普遍的吸引力及平凡人的快活，因為這首歌的命題可以是任何正經歷糟糕的一天的人<ref name="bbcm">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/7518881.stm|title=Secrets of writing a 'wallpaper' hit|author=Connor, Alan|date=2008-07-22|work=[[BBC_News_Magazine|BBC News Magazine]]|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|access-date=2014-12-19|archive-date=2022-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220202164239/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/7518881.stm}}</ref>。[[AllMusic|AllMusic]]的史蒂芬·湯瑪士·艾爾文（Stephen Thomas Erlewine）將歌曲描述為「一首悠揚、陽光明媚的曲調，與標題有著幾近相反的情緒」<ref name="all2" />。雖然[[About.com|About.com]]的比爾·蘭姆描述〈壞天氣〉使人「安定、欣慰」<ref>{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter – Daniel Powter|url=http://top40.about.com/od/albums/fr/dpowter.htm|access-date=2015-01-16|author=Lamb, Bill|work=[[About.com|About.com]]|publisher=[[IAC_(company)|IAC]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305011400/http://top40.about.com/od/albums/fr/dpowter.htm|archive-date=2016-03-05}}</ref>，但帕德表示這首歌是「嘲笑自我中心和自戀的人，他們總是抱怨東抱怨西」<ref name="times" />。他更坦言：「這不是字面意義上糟糕的一天，更多的是不要把自己太當回事，並抱怨枝微末節的瑣事。」<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews/hi/newsid_4730000/newsid_4734400/4734447.stm|title=Newsround speaks to pop star Daniel Powter|author=Boyton, Cristina|work=[[Newsround|Newsround]]|publisher=[[CBBC_(TV_channel)|CBBC]]|date=2005-08-01|access-date=2015-02-09|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203071151/http://news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews/hi/newsid_4730000/newsid_4734400/4734447.stm}}</ref>

== 專業評價 ==
〈壞天氣〉獲得褒貶不一的評價，一些評論家稱讚它的作曲，另一些則認為歌詞過於淺薄。《[[告示牌_(雜誌)|告示牌]]》的{{Le|查克·泰勒|Chuck Taylor (music journalist)}}稱這首歌「令人難忘」，並稱其為「優雅、永恆的流行/搖滾」，泰勒將其列為「年度最偉大的發現之一」<ref name="ct" />，而{{Le|皮特·沃特曼|Pete Waterman}}2007年在《[[衛報|衛報]]》刊文，稱其為他近年來最喜歡的歌曲之一<ref name="waterman">{{cite web|title=Today's music business is selfish and greedy|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2007/aug/10/todaysmusicbusinessisselfi|access-date=2014-12-19|author=Waterman, Pete|date=2007-08-10|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|publisher=[[Guardian_Media_Group|Guardian Media Group]]|archive-date=2022-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220202205202/https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2007/aug/10/todaysmusicbusinessisselfi}}</ref>。《{{Le|哈特福德新聞報|Hartford Courant}}》的艾瑞克·R·丹頓（Eric R. Danton）將其列為專輯中的最佳曲目<ref name="all2" /><ref>{{cite web|title='Idol' Exposure Benefits Powter|url=http://articles.courant.com/2006-05-25/entertainment/0605250543_1_american-idol-daniel-powter-bad-day|access-date=2015-02-09|author=Danton, Eric R.|date=2006-05-25|work=[[Hartford_Courant|Hartford Courant]]|publisher=[[Tribune_Company|Tribune Company]]|archive-date=2015-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150212060952/http://articles.courant.com/2006-05-25/entertainment/0605250543_1_american-idol-daniel-powter-bad-day}}</ref>，而艾爾文則稱其為「他處女作其餘部分的模板」。相比之下，威爾遜·孔（Wilson Kung）稱這首歌「與專輯中一些真正厲害的歌曲相比相形見絀」<ref name="popm" />。《BBC新聞雜誌》的艾倫·康納（Alan Connor）稱這是一首典型的感傷歌曲，但在〈壞天氣〉的案例中「細節太少了，有些對聯感覺像是從外語翻譯過來的，可能是機器翻譯的」<ref name="bbcm2">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/7518881.stm|title=Secrets of writing a 'wallpaper' hit|author=Connor, Alan|date=2008-07-22|work=[[BBC_News_Magazine|BBC News Magazine]]|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|access-date=2014-12-19|archive-date=2022-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220202164239/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/7518881.stm}}</ref>。《The Daily Edge》的作家稱其為「一首甜到你蛀牙的歌曲」<ref name="edge">{{cite web|title=One-hit wonders of the noughties: A definitive ranking from worst to best|url=http://www.dailyedge.ie/ranking-00s-one-hit-wonders-1321281-Mar2014/|access-date=2015-02-10|date=2014-03-08|work=The Daily Edge|publisher=[[TheJournal.ie|TheJournal.ie]]|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203234049/https://www.dailyedge.ie/ranking-00s-one-hit-wonders-1321281-Mar2014/}}</ref>，而《[[苏格兰人报|苏格兰人报]]》的評論家則指其「駭人」<ref>{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter|url=http://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/culture/music/daniel-powter-1-685285|access-date=2015-02-10|date=2005-12-22|work=[[The_Scotsman|The Scotsman]]|archive-date=2017-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170703183620/http://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/culture/music/daniel-powter-1-685285}}</ref>。比爾·蘭姆稱歌曲「感覺很真實」，但「如果你在尋找深度，這不是你的歌」<ref>{{cite web|title=Daniel Powter – Bad Day|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/baddaypowter.htm|access-date=2015-01-16|author=Lamb, Bill|work=About.com|publisher=IAC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924085009/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/baddaypowter.htm|archive-date=2015-09-24}}</ref>，《[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]]》的克里斯·李（Chris Lee）稱這首歌「有害但深情」<ref>{{cite web|title=A timely take on Lebanon|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2006/jul/30/entertainment/ca-fasttracks30|access-date=2015-02-11|author=Lee, Chris|date=2006-07-30|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|archive-date=2015-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150212063121/http://articles.latimes.com/2006/jul/30/entertainment/ca-fasttracks30}}</ref>，《[[時人|時人]]》評論：「〈壞天氣〉可能足夠朗朗上口，足以克服其陳腔濫調的歌詞」<ref>{{cite journal|title=Picks and Pans Review: Daniel Powter|url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20157296,00.html|date=2006-04-24|journal=[[People_(magazine)|People]]|publisher=[[Time_Inc|Time Inc]]|issue=16|volume=65|access-date=2015-02-05|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304105053/http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20157296,00.html}}</ref>。

== 音樂錄影帶 ==
[[音樂錄影帶|音樂錄影帶]]由[[馬克·偉柏|馬克·偉柏]]執導，於2005年初在[[雅虎|雅虎]]首播。截至2005年8月，影片的瀏覽次數已超過一百萬。2005年4月28日在[[VH1|VH1.com]]發布， 並於2005年12月13日在[[iTunes_Store|iTunes Store]]提供數位下載。它於次年1月23日在電視頻道VH1首次亮相，連續兩週進入3月份的倒計時前20名，而後於2006年4月被[[循環播放|循環播放]]，每週點播數超過50次，5月減少到每週30次。影片在2006年擁有超過980萬的點閱率，是當時觀看次數最八多的音樂錄影帶。華納兄弟唱片於2009 年10月26日將影片上傳至[[YouTube|YouTube]]。截至2022年1月，影片的觀看次數已超過2億。

